author: kenney
msg: Updated the copying of 'par' artifacts; the servlet container
does NOT automatically add '.par' files in the WEB-INF/lib/
directory to the classpath. So the copy will rename
Note that the lastest public review of the Ejb3 spec
states that .par and .ejb3 archives should have a .jar
extension. There are some M2 complications in using 'jar'
as the type and/or file extension for ejb3 and par archives.
When those are resolved, the special par handling can be dropped.
